        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 3:01PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 301 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Dunlap to near Topeka.
Movement was southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elkhart, Goshen, Kendallville, Ligonier, Syracuse, Dunlap, Albion,
Rome City, Topeka, Millersburg, New Paris, Benton, Wolcottville,
Cromwell, Brimfield, Honeyville, Foraker, Lake Wawasee, Waterford
Mills, and Lisbon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
